Interface IBytesConsumer

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ChunkReader, ChunkSeqBuffering, ChunkSeqReader, ChunkSeqReaderPng, ChunkSeqSkipping, DeflatedChunkReader

    public interface IBytesConsumer
    Bytes consumer. An object implementing can be fed with bytes. It can consume in steps, so each time it's fed with n bytes it can eat between 1 and n bytes.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      int consume(byte[] buf, int offset, int len)
      Eats some bytes, at most len (perhaps less).
      boolean isDone()
      The consumer is DONE when it does not need more bytes, either because it ended normally, or abnormally Typically this implies it will return -1 if consume() is called afterwards, but it might happen that it will consume more (unneeded) bytes anwyway

    • Method Detail

      • consume

        int consume(byte[] buf,
            int offset,
            int len)
        Eats some bytes, at most len (perhaps less).

        Returns bytes actually consumed. It returns -1 if the object didn't consume bytes because it was done or closed It should only returns 0 if len is 0

        boolean isDone()
        The consumer is DONE when it does not need more bytes, either because it ended normally, or abnormally Typically this implies it will return -1 if consume() is called afterwards, but it might happen that it will consume more (unneeded) bytes anwyway
